duties_responsibilities.duty: Process and review detailed and technical forms, files, etc., associated with multiple departmental programs or program areas under general supervision.
Provide sensitive and detailed program information and/or direction to the public, employees, employers, medical providers, and clients as a significant part of duties.
Identify and report suspected fraudulent claims/activities.
May perform duties for other specialized work or projects.
Demonstrate an awareness of the Department and Branch vision, mission, values, and goals.

education_certification.credential: Associate's degree in a relevant field (Bachelor's degree preferred)
